<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - SPEEDOMETER SIGNAL
        - FAULT CODES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT CODES</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If the vehicle speedometer does not operate properly, but no fault codes are present, use the
                    Prolink to attempt to read vehicle speed from the ATA data link connector. If vehicle speed can be
                    read using the Prolink, troubleshoot circuit 47B and the instrument cluster.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef12518173">3.180</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            and
            <emph type="bold">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="et1251830">3.35</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the circuit diagram and table for the voltage reference circuits.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef12518173" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg7112" filename="../figeg7/eg7112.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.180 - Vehicle Speed Sensor Circuit Diagram</caption>
        </figure>
